{"pageProps":{"frontmatter":{"layout":"ballerina-newsletter","issue":"2022 Issue #7 - August","title":"Ballerina Coding Challenge","description":"This is a periodic newsletter on Ballerina with hand-picked content and regular updates on the language.","keywords":"ballerina, community, ballerina community, newsletter","permalink":"/community/newsletter/2022-7/"},"content":"\n<table align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#FAFAFA\" class=\"bgtest\" style=\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;mso-table-lspace: 0pt;mso-table-rspace: 0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\n\t\t\t<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" id=\"templateHeader\" style=\"max-width: 950px;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;mso-table-lspace: 0pt;mso-table-rspace: 0pt;\" width=\"100%\">\n\t\t\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td align=\"left\" class=\"headerContent\" style=\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;mso-table-lspace: 0pt;mso-table-rspace: 0pt;color: #505050;font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 20px;font-weight: bold;line-height: 20px;text-align: left;vertical-align: middle;padding: 60px 10px 60px 10px;\" valign=\"top\"><a href=\"https://ballerina.io/?utm_source=mailer&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=mailer_email_ballerina_nwsltr_aug22_220831\" style=\" border: 0;text-decoration:none;\"><img alt=\"Ballerina Newsletter\" class=\"darkLogo\" height=\"28\" src=\"https://wso2.cachefly.net/wso2/sites/all/images/2020/ballerina-dark-logo.png\" style=\"display: inline-block;height: 28px;\" width=\"288\"></a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"mobile\" style=\"mso-hide: all; overflow: hidden; max-height: 0; width: 0; display: none; line-height: 0; visibility: hidden;\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div align=\"left\" class=\"lightLogo\" style=\"display:none; overflow:hidden; float:left; width:0px; max-height:0px; max-width:0px; line-height:0px; visibility:hidden;\"><a href=\"https://ballerina.io/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Ballerina Newsletter\" class=\"lightLogo\" height=\"28\" src=\"https://wso2.cachefly.net/wso2/sites/all/images/2020/ballerina-light-logo.png\" style=\"display: none;overflow: hidden;float: left;width: 0px;max-height: 0px;max-width: 0px;line-height: 0px;visibility: hidden;height: 28px;mso-hide:all;\" width=\"288\"></a></div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"darkintro\" style=\"color: #585a5e;display: block;font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;font-weight: 500;line-height: 24px;margin: 0;text-align: left;padding-top: 8px;padding-bottom: 10px;\">Issue #7 - August 31, 2022</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"darkintro\" style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #585a5e;line-height: 20px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;font-style: italic;\">This is a recurring newsletter of content around Ballerina and related technology topics such as integration, microservices, distributed systems, and cloud computing.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tNot a subscriber yet? <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://ballerina.io/community/ballerina-newsletter/?utm_source=mailer&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=mailer_email_ballerina_nwsltr_aug22_220831\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Sign up here</a>.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 26px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 28px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-bottom: 23px;padding-top: 30px;\">The Ballerina Coding Challenge</h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 10px;\">Global registrations are now open for the <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://bit.ly/3puWU9m\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Ballerina Coding Challenge</a>. This hackathon will take place from <span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Thursday, September 22 - Sunday, September 25, 2022</span> and is open to anyone interested in discovering the language's strengths in cloud native programming. <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://bit.ly/3puWU9m\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Register today</a> and stand a chance to win up to $10,000 in prizes!</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 26px; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87); line-height: 21px; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 40px;\">Data Manipulation with Functional Programming and Queries in Ballerina</h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 10px;\">In his latest <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://www.infoq.com/articles/ballerina-data-functional-programming\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">InfoQ article</a>, <a class=\"linkbody darklink\" href=\"https://twitter.com/viebel\" style=\"color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Yehonathan Sharvit</a> goes deeper into functional programming (FP) capabilities in Ballerina and explores an innovative way to use Ballerina’s query language to express data manipulation logic and discusses a data structure called “table”.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 26px; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87); line-height: 21px; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 40px;\">A Guide for Date/Time Conversions in Ballerina</h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 10px;\">Here's a <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/collectives/wso2/articles/73277351/a-guide-for-date-time-conversion-in-ballerina-language\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">guide</a> by WSO2 Software Engineer, Sahan Hemachandra, that covers the string manipulations required for the conversion of time formats into Ballerina time representations.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 26px; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87); line-height: 21px; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 40px;\">Secure a Ballerina REST API with OpenID Connect using Asgardeo</h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 10px;\">In this <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/collectives/wso2/articles/73300996/secure-a-ballerina-rest-api-with-openid-connect-using-asgardeo\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">tutorial</a>, Associate Director - Developer Advocacy at WSO2, <a class=\"linkbody darklink\" href=\"https://twitter.com/techieducky\" style=\"color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Dakshitha Ratnayake</a>, shows how to secure a Ballerina REST API by configuring JSON Web Token authentication for OpenID Connect with <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://wso2.com/asgardeo/?utm_source=mailer&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=mailer_email_ballerina_nwsltr_aug22_220831\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Asgardeo</a> as its identity provider.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 26px; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87); line-height: 21px; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 40px;\">Upcoming events</h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 21px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 25px;font-weight: 500;text-align: left;margin-bottom: 25px;padding-top: 25px;\">DeveloperWeek Cloud 2022</h3>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h4 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 16px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 20px;margin-bottom: 0;font-weight: 600;\">Wednesday, September 7, 2022 | 4.00 p.m. (CDT)</h4>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 9px;\">Catch WSO2 Senior Director, Platform Architecture, <a class=\"linkbody darklink\" href=\"https://twitter.com/sameerajayasoma\" style=\"color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Sameera Jayasoma</a>, at <a class=\"linkbody darklink\" href=\"https://www.developerweek.com/global/conference/cloud/\" style=\"color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">DeveloperWeek Cloud 2022</a> on <span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Wednesday, September 7, 2022, LIVE in Austin, Texas</span> at 4.00 p.m. (CDT), and <span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">virtually on Wednesday, September 14, 2022</span>. Sameera will be presenting <span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">“Ballerina: A Programming Language Designed for Cloud-Native Applications”</span>. Click <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://www.developerweek.com/global/conference/cloud/schedule/\" style=\"color: #20b6af;text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> for the full schedule.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 26px; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87); line-height: 21px; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 40px;\">Featured Tweets</h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 10px;\">In this month’s Featured tweets, we are spotlighting <a class=\"linkbody darklink\" href=\"https://twitter.com/tedneward\" style=\"color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);text-decoration: underline;font-weight: 600\" target=\"_blank\">@Tedneward</a>, <a class=\"linkbody darklink\" href=\"https://twitter.com/stalinkay\" style=\"color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);text-decoration: underline;font-weight: 600\" target=\"_blank\">@stalinkay</a>, and <a class=\"linkbody darklink\" href=\"https://twitter.com/davidfowl\" style=\"color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);text-decoration: underline;font-weight: 600\" target=\"_blank\">@DavidFowler</a> for showing us how they use Ballerina. Thanks again for your support!</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://twitter.com/tedneward/status/1554205312814440450\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Featured Tweets @Tedneward\" class=\"fadeimg\" height=\"364\" id=\"headerImage\" src=\"https://wso2.cachefly.net/wso2/sites/all/2022-optimized/b-nl-aug-tweet-image-1.png\" style=\"max-width: 215px;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;height: auto;outline: none;text-decoration: none;width: 100%;vertical-align: top;margin-top: 5px;border-radius: 6px;\" width=\"305\"></a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/stalinkay/status/1550434117615067138\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Featured Tweets @stalinkay\" class=\"fadeimg\" height=\"241\" id=\"headerImage\" src=\"https://wso2.cachefly.net/wso2/sites/all/2022-optimized/b-nl-aug-tweet-image-2.png\" style=\"max-width: 306px;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;height: auto;outline: none;text-decoration: none;width: 100%;vertical-align: top;margin-top: 5px;border-radius: 6px;\" width=\"306\"></a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/davidfowl/status/1560760124242661376\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Featured Tweets @DavidFowler\" class=\"fadeimg\" height=\"181\" id=\"headerImage\" src=\"https://wso2.cachefly.net/wso2/sites/all/2022-optimized/b-nl-aug-tweet-image-3.png\" style=\"max-width: 306px;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;height: auto;outline: none;text-decoration: none;width: 100%;vertical-align: top;margin-top: 5px;border-radius: 6px;\" width=\"306\"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 26px; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87); line-height: 21px; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 40px;\">Support Us</h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 10px;\">Join our community and get to know the latest news about Ballerina by following us on <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://twitter.com/ballerinalang\" style=\"color: #20b6af;\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>. Mention <span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">@ballerinalang</span> with the hashtag <span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">#ballerinalang</span> when you tweet about us and have a chance of being featured in our newsletter! Don’t forget to subscribe to our <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/Ballerinalang\" style=\"color: #20b6af;\" target=\"_blank\">YouTube</a> channel.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-top: 20px;padding-bottom: 1.5rem;\">You can also show us your support by starring <a class=\"linkbody\" href=\"https://github.com/ballerina-platform/ballerina-lang\" style=\"color: #20b6af;\" target=\"_blank\">Ballerina’s GitHub repo</a> and following us.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"font-family: 'Roboto', Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;color: rgba(0,0,0,0.87);line-height: 21px;font-weight: 400;text-align: left;margin-bottom: 0;padding-bottom: 2.5rem;\">Until next month,<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tThe Ballerina Team</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t\t\t</table>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n"},"__N_SSG":true}